##The line of fire | them: The team that worked out the clues to the outbreak

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

The purpose of epidemic survey is to obtain the information of the patients'medical history, travel history and contact history, and to provide the key basis for analyzing the transmission route and controlling the further spread of epidemic situation.

Reporter | Wang Yu

Yang Yufan and Jiang Tingan, two young staff members of the Changning District Center for Disease Control and Prevention in Shanghai, walked into the dining hall after handing over the Specimens and taking off a full set of protective gear. It was the evening of January 30, and the two girls had just finished an epidemiological investigation of a suspected case of new crown pneumonia ("flow") and the task of transporting specimens.

They were back in time for dinner, and they were on call 24 hours a day. No matter day or night, as long as the relevant hospital in the area of suspected cases of information sent, they immediately armed to the scene, into the isolation ward, and suspected patients to communicate closely. Disease Control Workers, perhaps outside of the front line medical staff, are the closest group to the outbreak.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Staff of the Changning District CDC (second from Right) and Beijing Tongren Hospital medical workers at the scene of the new crown pneumonia epidemic on January 26,2010 in Changning District

The purpose of epidemic survey is to obtain the information of the patients'medical history, travel history and contact history, and to provide the key basis for analyzing the transmission route and controlling the further spread of epidemic situation. For example, once a suspected patient has been diagnosed, CDC staff immediately follow the flow of information obtained, looking for patients who have been in close contact with the confirmed patient, to take appropriate medical observation and other measures.

So they have to be as thorough as possible. Where the suspected patient has been in the recent past, who he has been in close contact with, the frequency of the means of transport used, and so on, as much detail as possible. When the other party do not remember clearly, they also want to try to help each other try to remember. It usually takes anywhere from half an hour to an hour to make a switch, not including the time it takes to put on and off the protective gear.

After the transfer, if they need to take samples from suspected patients, they have to wait for the hospital to take samples, and put on a new set of protective equipment, the samples will be sent back to the CDC for testing. At present, the district-level CDC in Shanghai has been able to test samples of suspected cases of NCP on its own, and the microbiological laboratory of Changning District CDC is operating round-the-clock to provide test results as soon as possible.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Changning District Center for Disease Control and prevention staff dressed in protective equipment, ready to set off on a sampling mission photograph: Wang Yu

In Normal Times, the staff of the Infectious Disease Prevention and Control Division are the main ones to carry out the transfer, and they are the first echelon, said Cai Enmao, deputy director of the Changning District CDC, second-tier personnel from other departments also go directly to the front line.

Yang Yufan and Jiang Tingan are usually members of the second echelon. Just over a year, two years of their respective occupation, they told the Xinmin Weekly reporter, just finished this task, is the first time the two really into the flow of the scene.

"Although we have participated in many rehearsals before, we are still a little nervous to face a real battle and such a major epidemic. We just keep reminding ourselves to be careful and not make mistakes, " Yang said. Wearing protective clothing is not breathable, in the goggles of the vision is not very clear, not very clear record form, these are they try to overcome.

About the risk of contracting the virus at work, Yang Yufan said: "This is the responsibility we should have to assume and face, fear is also no way to fear. "

Jiang said that her family knew she was going to the front line and had always told her to protect herself, "so I definitely need to practice my skills and protect myself. " She said that her family also understood that it was her duty to do this, she has to do it.

In addition to the transfer in recent days, the two of them have been working in the data group. "Busy every day, and do not have time to think about too much else. " However, they still meet in the field task, wearing red clothes. "We hope it will be better, " they said, laughing.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Yang Yufan (right) and Jiang Tingan of the Changning District Center for Disease Control and Prevention on the evening of January 30,2006, after performing the mission of collecting and transporting specimens, by Wang Yu

The girls said their courage and confidence also came from strong support from their colleagues. "Our leaders and colleagues have been working overtime these days, and one of them has been working almost all night. Not only has she stuck to her post, she has also given us very practical experience in transferring staff. "

The "on-the-go" colleague they're referring to is the last remaining arm of Changning District's Disease Control. On January 26, at about 10:30 pm on the second day of the Lunar New Year, the remaining man on duty received the transfer assignment and immediately rushed to the Beijing Tongren Hospital. The suspected patient is an 80-year-old grandmother, breathing heavily, said a sentence or two will be short of breath, the dialogue process is slow. After patiently asking all the questions, Yu returned to the CDC, finished the flow report and passed the review, it was already after 3:00 the next morning. She grabbed a few hours, after Dawn 7 o'clock, she put on protective clothing, carrying a specimen box to the city disease control send samples.

Still, she was working on how to do the job better. Yu Li is usually in the center of the "Popular Science Master" , a hand painting and production of video "skills" , she thought, can try the flow of the whole process into a small video, to share to the scene of the partners.

On the night of January 28th she had an idea, and the next day she and her colleagues set to work. Colleagues to the Beijing Tongren Hospital, and other locations on the spot, back to draw a plan sketch, Yu Li on this basis processing, soon video to colleagues in the mobile phone. At the same time, Yu Li and his colleagues also put forward a new chart-text version of the "Gem" ————————————————————————————————————————————————————.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A home-made video capture of the flow process from the new crown flow team at the Changning District Center for Disease Control

The reporter from "Xinmin Weekly" saw that the entire flow of this "treasure book" is described in great detail, including where the hospital has what kind of equipment, which channel to go through, which door to open, where the specimen container was collected in the center was clearly recorded, and all the important contents were highlighted with a prominent background color, accompanied by a number of pictures. The video focuses on the flow of hospital ward on-site matters, with sound and dynamic elements, very useful. This set of pictures, text and video, has become a disease control and control team in Changning District, a copy, before the mission must study.

"The hardest thing these days is not getting enough sleep, which is an average of three to four hours a day, " Yu said, adding that many of Changning District's disease control workers did not get a single day off throughout this year's Lunar New Year holiday. The reporter from the Xinmin Weekly saw at the scene that many staff members of the Changning District Disease Control and prevention work continuously. There is a folding bed in the office of Zhao Wensui, director of the center, and Cai Enmao, deputy director of the center. They have been sleeping in the office for several days, never made it home.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Changning District Center for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) staff continue to fight the epidemic by Wang Yu

"This time I really feel that I can make a contribution to the public, and I feel my professional significance as a disease controller. We still have to fight the epidemic, " Yu said.
